天気予報 Archive.title: 季節変更
天気予報 Archive.about:
We do all our calculations in real time, but we have a few important things to keep in mind. Firstly, we look at the conditions we are seeing because it's very important for us to know where that wind will be blowing next week.
Then, if we want to know how much cloud cover is available from different locations in the day, we have to consider the length of the day. You cannot forecast where clouds will be at any particular moment - they are going to show up every morning as rain.
We also ask ourselves: 'what kind of conditions are there when this weather looks interesting and we might do something about it? What is the worst case scenario for us? Is it a windchill factor of four or nine or 10 degrees? Then we look at the next morning.'
For example, suppose that the next day's low of 15C is going to be very dry. If we have only 15C winds, we would want to know what their current conditions are...
- Yuji (Meteorologist, excerpt speech about discussion)

天気予報 Archive.title: Beyond The Veil (Farewell Performance)
天気予報 Archive.about:
SERIES X - ALBUM X
LINK EXPIRED
________________________________________________________
Creator Notes:
This is it…
Thank you for listening to [天気予報]. My words cannot describe how thankful I am for supporting this project throughout the years. As I packed up everything, I wanted to put up one final release as I couldn’t fulfill my promises. To make up for most of my false promises, I’ve created this titled “Beyond The Veil.”
Heavily inspired by Helmut Lang’s Make It Hard.
“The transition between the past and the future.”This LP is created by purposely destroying most of my [天気予報] physicals I’ve collected since inception and recording it if it is still audible (albeit with heavy use of effects from my pedals or others), with this, it destroys eight years of work with little to no remorse (made in one take).
It may sound comical or disgusting, and its primary purpose… to evoke a wide range of emotions. Love it or hate it, I’m satisfied with the final product, and destroying them is pretty fun.
Now that I’ve finished the first half, the second half is mostly some insights regarding my favourite [天気予報] albums that I want to share and some to reminisce about.
As you may know, [巡] is pretty much one of my favourite albums in the line, but it was merely an afterthought when thinking of continuing this project in the first place. It’s Virtual Polygon’s Imagine with added effects. Nonetheless, doing it in one session is pretty good, as most of the samples fit together, making one cohesive album. Moving from tracks to art, I’ve been on a rabbit hole of finding the origin of the [巡] album art… I can’t remember how many hours I’ve sunk on finding this CM from CM yearbooks to Betamax tapes. It's a 15-second CM with them pushing a yellow car to a hill. Nevertheless, I have yet to find it… If you found it give me an e-mail as I want to see it again.
[ひまわり画像], an album that needs no introduction. It almost got scrapped after months in production limbo during the summer of 2018. I announced in my own (now defunct) imprint that this will be out with 120 tracks on its belt. I decided to scrap the original plan and create it based on a typical TV broadcast schedule from early morning to midnight. It was a daunting task, but I pulled a crazy rollout with it. I do see people trying to decipher the samples I used. I’d say good luck (I did manage to identify half of the samples used).
Let's finish it where it all started: my debut album… wasn’t my favourite project then. It mostly started when I encountered a Cecile CM during my hunt for samples to use (Primarily for Virtual Polygon). I initially planned it as a Virtual Polygon Album for a particular label but scrapped it as it wouldn’t be a fit for Virtual Polygon. I am glad that I made that decision. If I chose the latter, [天気予報] wouldn’t have existed, and I wouldn’t have explored signalwave at all.
Alright, it's time to wrap up or else I could go on and on and bore you to death. Overall, Again, thank you so much and goodbye. Hopefully, we see each other again.
- 天気予報 (2017 - 2023)
- Noryokun (2013 - 2023)

天気予報 Archive.title: ひまわり衛星: Kizu Random
天気予報 Archive.about:
Sequel...
Thank you for supporting this little project that I created in 2017 as a pet project.
As a gift, I present to you... ひまわり衛星 The final asutenki album.
1 - 360: Morning / Kizu Random (Feb 3)
361 - 720: Afternoon / Kako Random (Feb 17)
721 - 1080: Night / Asu Random (Mar 2)
Total: 1080 (25+ Hours)
CM breaks: will be out ASAP (Track Errors)
Produced Date: 1/06/2017 - 1/3/2020 (updated due to track duplicates and a bunch of errors)

天気予報 Archive.title: ひまわり画像 (Myriad of Colours)
天気予報 Archive.about:
Hello,
To celebrate 天気予報's 4th "late" anniversary, happy to say that I'm re-releasing ひまわり画像 with some major (or minor) changes & some bonus tracks.
You may hate it or like it, but here's the final product. BTW, this project concluded in 2020, just a release to commemorate 天気予報 (late release but oh well...).
Nonetheless, thank you for supporting this project & have a great day.
-H

(Unreleased) ひまわり衛星: Asu Random - Track 4 @23:49
(early) Happy New Year.
This will be the Final track to be released here (As you may know, this project will cease operation after New Year's Day)... Decided to unearthed this as I found it in my old USB.
ひまわり衛星: ASU RANDOM was scrapped many times but this is the third iteration (2020-era).
Anyway, Thank you for supporting this project of mine.
(I've said too many goodbyes, anyway I'll be moving on).
- 天気予報 (2017 - 2023)
